The paper deals with deep neural networks for image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed architecture involves learning a latent hierarchy of classes, which is a task related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of one hot vectors for representing classes, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the grouping of visually similar classes, which is a task related to natural language processing (cs.CL).
